==Useful relations==

The hyperbolic functions satisfy many identities, all of them similar in form to the trigonometric identities. In fact, Osborn&#x27;s rule states that one can convert any trigonometric identity (up to but not including sinhs or implied sinhs of 4th degree) for formula_17, formula_18, formula_19 or formula_17 and formula_21 into a hyperbolic identity, by expanding it completely in terms of integral powers of sines and cosines, changing sine to sinh and cosine to cosh, and switching the sign of every term containing a product of two sinhs.

